<subsection xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="subsec-modulus-norm-of-a-complex">
<title>Modulus (Norm) of a complex number</title>
<definition xml:id="def-modulus-of-a-complex-number">
    <statement>
        <p>
            The modulus of a complex number z = x+iy is a non-negative real number denoted by |z| and is defined as |z| = <m>\sqrt{x^{2} + y^{2}}</m>. Geometrically, the number |z| represents the distnce between the point (x, y) and the origin.
        </p>
    </statement>
</definition>

